This is a known breaking change. In .NET 10, MAUI enables **edge-to-edge** display on Android by default, which makes the old `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` mode ineffective. The window no longer physically resizes when the keyboard appears.

## Fix: Use `WindowInsets` to react to the keyboard

In your Android platform code (e.g., `Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs`), use `ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener` to detect keyboard (IME) insets and adjust your page's bottom padding:

```csharp
using Android.Views;
using AndroidX.Core.View;
using Microsoft.Maui.Platform;

// In your MainActivity or a custom handler:
protected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)
{
    base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);

    var rootView = Window!.DecorView.FindViewById(Android.Resource.Id.Content)!;

    ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(rootView, new KeyboardInsetsListener());
}

class KeyboardInsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener
{
    public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(Android.Views.View v, WindowInsetsCompat insets)
    {
        var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
        var navBarInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.NavigationBars());

        // Use the larger of IME or nav-bar bottom inset
        int bottom = Math.Max(imeInsets.Bottom, navBarInsets.Bottom);
        v.SetPadding(0, 0, 0, bottom);

        return insets;
    }
}
```

## Why this works

| .NET 9 | .NET 10 |
|---|---|
| `AdjustResize` shrinks the window | Edge-to-edge: window stays full-screen |
| Layout auto-adjusts | You consume **WindowInsets** yourself |

## Alternative: opt out of edge-to-edge (quick workaround)

In `Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs`:

```csharp
protected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)
{
    base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);
    // Revert to legacy resize behavior
    Window!.SetSoftInputMode(Android.Views.SoftInput.AdjustResize);
}
```

> ⚠️ This is a stopgap — Google deprecated `AdjustResize` in API 30 and edge-to-edge is the future. The insets approach is the recommended long-term fix.
